# Multi-Agent Development Rules

## Task Management

- Read assigned task file from docs/tasks/agent-X-\*.md
- Update task status: TODO → IN_PROGRESS → DONE
- Add lock before starting: [LOCKED by Agent X at YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]
- Remove lock when done
- Stop when: all tasks DONE + no errors + doc updated

## Code Standards

- Follow existing patterns in codebase
- Use shadcn/ui components (see src/components/ui/)
- Use React Query hooks (see src/hooks/)
- Follow TypeScript strict mode
- Use existing Supabase types (src/integrations/supabase/types.ts)

## Design Patterns

- DRY: Reuse existing hooks and components
- SOLID: Single responsibility, dependency injection via hooks
- Component structure: See src/pages/ for examples
- Hook structure: See src/hooks/useFamilies.ts for pattern

## Documentation

- Reference business rules: docs/BUSINESS_RULES.md
- Reference frontend tasks: docs/FRONTEND_TASKS.md
- Reference API patterns: docs/API_INTEGRATION.md
- Update task file with progress
- No duplicate information across docs

## Commands to AVOID

- Do NOT run: npm run dev, npm start, npm install
- Do NOT commit changes
- Do NOT modify .cursorrules or task files of other agents

